RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 2 1 1/16M Turf CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 37200. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000, if for $24,000, allowed 4 lbs. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race on the Turf course, it will be run o n the main track at One Mile).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AWESOME STRIKE steadied early, edged up then waited near the far turn, dropped in to quickly gain, angled out past the five sixteenths, forged five wide outside foes and took command in mid stretch, kicked away and was kept to task. ELUSIVE , between foes early, was put to a ride while in the clear into the far turn, angled out, circled four wide with chase into the lane, shifted out widert for the final furlong, kept on with good energy and nabbed the place at the wire. HAY CHIEF , taken back to be well off the early pace, saved ground to the lane, eased out and split rivals in mid stretch then continued on willingly. STELLAR LUTE , well placed stalking inside, eased out and edged up behind the duelers into the stretch, chased then flattened out late. GIANTSBANE settled off the inside, gained four wide past the three eighths, bid three deep into the lane, vied past mid stretch then weakened. LONGWORTH lagged back, circled the second turn and had a belated run. IMAGINE IT steadied early, edged up off the rail then was stalled behind a tiring rival near the three eighths, dropped in but lacked a solid recovery. NORTH HIGHLAND , between rivals early, stalked the pace, bid to a short lead past the five sixteenths, dueled into the lane then weakened in mid stretch. GETTIN'DOWNONIT was sent wide to clear, dropped in and set the pace, was collared past the three eighths, vied inside foes into the lane then tired. SILK PRINCE , sent from the gate, rated off of the leader under the wire the first time, raced three deep into the backstretch and faltered.

(If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race on the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Eighth) (Rail at 52 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWO BY TWO settled well back of the dueling leaders while saving ground, took closer order cutting the corner into the lane, angled out and edged up behind foes, shifted out further and worked through between horses near the sixteenth pole, surged under solid hand asking when clear and just got up. SUPER E settled far back while saving ground, continued inside and progressed past the three sixteenths, stayed towards the rail and forged clear in deep stretch, kept on gamely but was nipped at the wire. BRILLIANT CHASE rated behind foes early, edged up between runners into the far turn, advanced three wide into the lane, altered in for the final furlong and churned on. TRANSIT secured the inside into the first turn and raced closest to the embattled leaders, gained under a ride and to the inside of a rival past the five sixteenths, shifted out for the drive, had aim in mid stretch but one paced late. PAPAL LAW , away alertly, got into a duel to the inside of GUNSLINGER (IRE) passing the wire for the first time, carried that battle into the lane, wandered outward while going head to head past mid stretch then faded late. GUNSLINGER (IRE) broke inward and tossed his a head a bit when corrected, engaged PAPAL LAW from the outside early on, sparred past mid stretch then weakened late. DANCING TIL DUSK , three deep early while off the duel, gained four wide into the stretch to loom, failed to sustain near mid stretch, drifted out and weakened. DOWN COLD , wide and under a ride into the far turn, faltered, was eased through the final furlong then vanned off.

Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $45,000, if for $36,000, allowed 4 lbs. Registered MD-Bred and/or MD-Sired horses may waive claiming price in th is race. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race on the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile) (Rail at 52 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARMEL SUNRISE vied inside a rival early on, was deftly rated back off the lead and angled out to track, edged up into the far turn, went on the attack near the five sixteenths, wrested command into the lane, spurted clear under a drive then held firm through the final furlong. TANKA TOUGH rated well back past the three quarter pole, gained along the rail into the far turn, sustained past the five sixteenths, eased out with pursuit, raced on her left lead past the furlong grounds but kept on willingly to the wire. NAMI had speed between foes into the first turn then rated back off the leaders, edged up just off the inside into the far turn, angled three wide to have aim into the stretch then went evenly through the final sixteenth. KRONE broke a step slow, moved up between runners past the half, angled out, circled four wide into the stretch, shifted back in and kept on with effort. FORGOTTEN GIFT , between foes early, dropped in to save ground through the backstretch, checked when trying to advance into the far turn, recovered to save ground past the five sixteenths, swung out in upper stretch and finished with interest. QUEEN OF THE DANCE lost ground four wide, edged up nearing the far turn, dropped in some to pursue, bumped with a rival in mid stretch then flattened out. TIME GOES FAST , wide, was floated out around the far turn, remained wide for the drive and had a slight gain. CATCH THE KITTEN rated two wide, moved up near the half mile pole, checked in tight soon after, checked again and bumped with a rival in mid stretch then kept on trying while towards the inside the final seventy yards. NUWANDA vied outside a pair of runners before clearing, opened up past the three quarter pole, set the pace towards the rail, was engaged near the five sixteenths and weakened past the three sixteenths. GINGER GIRL , four wide, was not a factor. SMOKE N SIN was outrun. ALWAYS FORWARD , between runners, was taken up near the far turn.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPYCRAFT , quickly to the front, set a rated pace towards the inside, handled outside pressure around the turn, responded when put to asking past the quarter pole, opened up under a drive leaving mid stretch and held firm. HUNTER JOE rated off the inside, raced between foes nearing the lane, swung out five wide and closed steadily to earn the place in the final yards. BY THE SEY SHORE rated off the pace while saving ground, worked outward to be about four wide in upper stretch, closed to the inside of HUNTER JOE but was out kicked by that one for second. BOSS IS A PAL , well placed while saving ground just off the leaders, failed to kick on under pressure in mid stretch and faded. SO STREET prompted the pace two to three wide outside the winner, saw that one get away past the three sixteenths and faded. VALIANT VINNY broke in the air, regrouped and edged up four wide into the turn, circled stalking the leaders into the stretch, gave hard chase past mid stretch and faded.
